ice%20Association%2C%20which%20represent%20government%20employees%2C%20as%20well%20as%20by%20anti-poverty%20organization%20Oxfam%20America.%20They%20allege%20that%20Trump%20overstepped%20his%20authority%20in%20largely%20shuttering%20an%20independent%20agency%20established%20by%20Congress%20by%20firing%20or%20putting%20on%20leave%20its%20employees%20and%20cancelling%20its%20agreements%20with%20third-party%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20on%20Tuesday%20asked%20US%20District%20Judge%20Carl%20Nichols%20for%20a%20temporary%20restraining%20order%20blocking%20the%20destruction%20of%20records.%20They%20said%20that%20if%20they%20eventually%20prevail%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20vital%20personnel%20or%20other%20records%20could%20prevent%20USAID%20from%20resuming%20its%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20Tuesday's%20motion%2C%20the%20judge%20ordered%20both%20sides%20to%20submit%20a%20status%20report%20by%20Wednesday%20morning%20proposing%20a%20schedule%20for%20briefs%20on%20the%20motion%20and%20noting%20any%20disagreements%20between%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENichols%2C%20a%20Trump%20appointee%2C%20last%20month%20allowed%20the%20administration%20to%20go%20forward%20with%20its%20plan%20to%20put%20more%20than%202%2C000%20USAID%20employees%20on%20leave.%20Under%20Trump%2C%20the%20foreign%20aid%20agency%20has%20scrapped%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20its%20programs%20and%20fired%20much%20of%20its%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20lawsuit%20brought%20by%20USAID%20contractors%20and%20grant%20recipients%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20on%20Monday%20ruled%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20cannot%20refuse%20to%20spend%20foreign%20aid%20money%20appropriated%20by%20Congress%2C%20although%20the%20judge%20stopped%20short%20of%20restoring%20canceled%20contracts.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20repeatedly%20resisted%20complying%20with%20court%20orders%20to%20release%20frozen%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3