s%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-lessons-wish-learned-wealthy-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20and%20terms%20apply%20to%20offers%20listed%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F637bdb29da9aea00181d82cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22320%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Holly%20Johnson.%3Cp%3EHolly%20Johnson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20on%20track%20to%20retire%20wealthy%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20always%20smart%20with%20our%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20wish%20we'd%20started%20investing%20sooner%2C%20and%20learned%20earlier%20that%20we%20could%20make%20more%20working%20for%20ourselves.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI've%20also%20learned%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20make%20some%20bad%20decisions%20and%20still%20do%20fine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20started%20getting%20serious%20about%20our%20finances%20in%20our%20late%2020s%2C%20we%20naturally%20thought%20we%20had%3Cem%3E%20everything%3C%2Fem%3E%20figured%20out.%20We%20believed%20we%20would%20live%20intensely%20frugal%20lives%20and%20work%20toward%20paying%20off%20every%20cent%20of%20debt%20we%20had%2C%20and%20that's%20exactly%20what%20we%20did.%20However%2C%20we%20never%20thought%20much%20about%20what%20happens%20next%2C%20or%20how%20our%20attitudes%20about%20money%20might%20dramatically%20change%20as%20we%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%2C%20we%20became%20self-employed%20somewhere%20along%20the%20way%20and%20started%20earning%20more%20money.%20And%20now%20that%20I'm%2043%2C%20I%20can%20say%20with%20certainty%20that%20we're%20financially%20independent%20and%20on%20track%20to%20retire%20wealthy%20when%20our%20kids%20leave%20the%20house%20in%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20there%20are%20some%20lessons%20I%20learned%20in%20my%2030s%20and%20early%2040s%20that%20I%20wish%20had%20clicked%20earlier%2C%20and%20for%20more%20reasons%20than%20one.%20Here's%20an%20overview%20of%20what%20I%20wish%20I'd%20known%20about%20money%20when%20I%20was%20younger%2C%20and%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22967c09e2-88e6-4d8e-bb7f-ab048653966c%5C%22%3E1.%20Earning%20more%20money%20changes%20everything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20lesson%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20learned%20earlier%20is%20just%20how%20impactful%20it%20can%20be%20to%20increase%20your%20earnings%2C%20especially%20since%20I%20only%20earned%20around%20%2440%2C000%20at%20my%20old%209-to-5%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20anyone%20says%20to%20the%20contrary%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20you%20can%20save%20when%20you're%20on%20a%20fixed%20income.%20You%20can%20cut%20your%20cable%20bill%20and%20start%20using%20a%20monthly%20meal%20plan.%20From%20there%2C%20other%20steps%20like%20buying%20a%20smaller%20home%20and%20shopping%20around%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fauto-insurance%2Fbest-cheap-car-insurance-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecar%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fbest-homeowners-insurance-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomeowners%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20only%20save%20so%20much.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20worse%2C%20working%20in%20a%20traditional%209-to-5%20job%20also%20means%20getting%20whatever%20raise%20you're%20assigned%20to%20receive%20each%20year%2C%20if%20you%20get%20one%20at%20all.%20At%20my%20old%20job%20from%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20I%20was%20pretty%20much%20limited%20to%20a%203%25%20raise%20each%20year%2C%20no%20matter%20what.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20earn%20more%20money%20can%20solve%20myriad%20problems%20while%20helping%20you%20invest%20for%20the%20future%20on%20a%20much%20faster%20timeline.%20If%20I%20could%20go%20back%20and%20change%20anything%20in%20this%20realm%2C%20I%20would%20have%20left%20my%20traditional%20job%20to%20become%20self-employed%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20instead%20of%20spending%20years%20wondering%20if%20I%20would%20be%20making%20the%20right%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20aren't%20interested%20in%20self-employment%2C%20finding%20other%20ways%20to%20earn%20more%20can%20be%20a%20huge%20deal.%20This%20could%20mean%20taking%20on%20overtime%20at%20work%2C%20picking%20up%20a%20side%20hustle%2C%20or%20switching%20jobs%20to%20secure%20higher%20pay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260abe87a-f983-4ac9-9b3f-18a35cec7aa9%5C%22%3E2.%20The%20power%20of%20compound%20interest%20is%20astonishing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20lesson%20ties%20into%20the%20first%20one%2C%20but%20I%20really%20do%20wish%20we%20had%20begun%20investing%20for%20retirement%20at%20a%20much%20younger%20age.%20We%20actually%20opened%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20our%20late%2020s%2C%20and%20we%20only%20contributed%20a%20nominal%20percentage%20of%20our%20incomes%20at%20the%20time.%20Now%20that%20I%20know%20and%20understand%20the%20magic%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20wish%20we%20had%20contributed%20much%20more%20than%20we%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20is%2C%20investing%20as%20regularly%20and%20early%20as%20possible%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20benefit%20from%20compound%20interest%20so%20you%20can%20retire%20when%20you%20want%2C%20and%20on%20your%20own%20terms.%20After%20all%2C%20investing%20early%20lets%20you%20begin%20building%20up%20a%20nest%20egg%20that%20increases%20in%20value%20over%20time%2C%20and%20compound%20interest%20eventually%20lets%20you%20grow%20wealth%20off%20of%20wealth%20you%20already%20earned%20on%20your%20investments%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20an%20example%2C%20consider%20this%20financial%20scenario%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you%20invest%20%241%2C500%20a%20month%20for%2030%20years%20starting%20at%20age%2030%2C%20which%20means%20you%20are%20making%20%24540%2C000%20in%20contributions%20over%20that%20time.%20If%20you%20earned%20an%20average%20yield%20of%207%25%2C%20you%20would%20end%20the%2030-year%20period%20at%20age%2060%20with%20just%20over%20%241.7%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20imagine%20you%20invest%20%242%2C250%20for%2020%20years%20starting%20at%20age%2040%2C%20which%20means%20you%20are%20making%20the%20same%20%24540%2C000%20in%20investments%20over%20a%20shorter%20timeline.%20With%20the%20same%207%25%20yield%2C%20you%20would%20end%20the%2020%20years%20at%20age%2060%20with%20just%20over%20%241.106%20million%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227762bd4-57cf-4250-b53b-bfefc8a2e9d1%5C%22%3E3.%20You%20can%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20bad%20decisions%20and%20still%20do%20fine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20made%20some%20really%20good%20financial%20decisions%2C%20we%20have%20made%20some%20pretty%20tragic%20ones%2C%20too.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20delayed%20investing%20for%20retirement%20as%20I%20already%20mentioned%2C%20and%20we%20overspent%20on%20remodeling%20our%20second%20home%20and%20sold%20it%20for%20a%20loss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20spent%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20trading%20in%20our%20cars%20for%20new%20ones%20during%20the%20first%20few%20years%20of%20our%20marriage%2C%20and%20we%20initially%20had%20our%20investments%20with%20a%20high-cost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%3C%2Fa%3E%20firm%20that%20charged%20pricey%20and%20unnecessary%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I've%20gotten%20older%2C%20however%2C%20I%20have%20realized%20you%20can%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20big%20mistakes%20and%20still%20do%20pretty%20well.%20You%20just%20have%20to%20have%20some%20good%20decisions%20mixed%20into%20the%20bad%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20ahead%26quot%3B%20slowly%20over%20time%2C%20even%20if%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20taking%20three%20steps%20forward%20and%20two%20steps%20back%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20made%20lots%20of%20great%20decisions%2C%20including%20venturing%20into%20self-employment%2C%20investing%20a%20ton%20during%20our%20highest%20earning%20years%2C%20and%20avoiding%20debt%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20and%20counting.%20While%20the%20mistakes%20from%20our%20past%20have%20held%20us%20back%20to%20a%20certain%20extent%2C%20the%20good%20decisions%20we%20have%20made%20more%20than%20made%20up%20for%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2206722a12-1300-41e4-b